{"id":1017,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1017,"title":"Ramah","subtitle":"","short_title":"Ramah","uri":"/scriptures/bd/ramah","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/ramah.t1","order":".000.3381"},[".title","Ramah"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/ramah.p1","order":".000.3382"},["i","Height."],"(1) A town, about the site of which there has been much dispute, in Benjamin, on the border of Ephraim (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/18.25"},"Josh. 18:25"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/4.5"},"Judg. 4:5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/19.13"},"19:13"],"); the home of Samuel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/1.19"},"1 Sam. 1:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/2.11"},"2:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/7.17"},"7:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.4"},"8:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/15.34"},"15:34"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/16.13"},"16:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/19.18-23"},"19:18–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/20.1"},"20:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/22.6"},"22:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/25.1"},"25:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/28.3"},"28:3"],"). Being on the frontier and on the road to Jerusalem, it was the scene of several conflicts between Israel and Judah (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/15.17,21-22"},"1 Kgs. 15:17, 21–22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/16.1,5-6"},"2 Chr. 16:1, 5–6"],"). At the time of the captivity the exiles were collected here before removal to Babylon (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/31.15"},"Jer. 31:15"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/40.1"},"40:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scr